        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:19PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 218 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Ivanhoe, or 8 miles north of Fries, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...

Locations impacted include...
Byllesby...
Ivanhoe...
Coleman Store...
and Woodlawn.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
